<p style="font-size:10.0pt;margin:0in 0in .0001pt;"><b><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;font-weight:bold;">Item 7.01</font></b><font size="1" style="font-size:3.0pt;">&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160; </font><b>Regulation FD Disclosure.</b></p>
<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>
<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;text-indent:.75in;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">Attached as Exhibit&nbsp;99.1 and furnished for purposes of Regulation FD is a presentation Select Medical Holdings Corporation (the &#147;Company&#148;) may use from time to time in presentations or discussions with investors, analysts and other parties after the date hereof in the third and fourth quarters of 2015. The presentation is substantively the same as the presentation filed with the Current Report on Form&nbsp;8-K on May&nbsp;20, 2015, with the exception of an update to slide 12, which reflects updated information recently received by the Company.</font></p>
<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>
<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;text-indent:.75in;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">The information in this Current Report on Form&nbsp;8-K (including Exhibit&nbsp;99.1) is being furnished solely to satisfy the requirements of Regulation FD and shall not be deemed to be &#147;filed&#148; for purposes of Section&nbsp;18 of the Securities Exchange Act of 1934 (the &#147;Exchange Act&#148;) or otherwise subject to the liabilities of that section, nor shall it be deemed to be incorporated by reference in any filing under the Securities Act of 1933 or the Exchange Act.</font></p>

<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;"><font size="1" color="white" face="Times New Roman" style="color:white;font-size:1.0pt;">LTACH   Legislation LTACH Patient Criteria passed in late December 2013 as part of   Budget bill and SGR - effective beginning Q4 2015 &#149; LTACH Rates for patients   with; &#149;3 day prior short term acute hospital ICU/CCU stay or &#149;Ventilation   patients for &gt; 96 hours in the LTACH Other patients receive &#147;site neutral&#148;   rate which &#149; is lesser of; &#149;IPPS per diem (capped at the IPPS DRG amount plus   outlier payment) or 100% cost &#149;Site Neutral payments phased in over 3 years   11 </font></p>    </td>   </tr>  </table>

<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;"><font size="1" color="white" face="Times New Roman" style="color:white;font-size:1.0pt;">Concentra   Investment Rationale &#149; &#149; &#149; Business well known by both WCAS and Select   Complementary to Select&#146;s outpatient rehabilitation business Significant   geographic overlap of Concentra centers and Select outpatient clinics   Select&#146;s track record of successful acquisitions combined with &#149; WCAS&#146;s   historical knowledge of Concentra provides meaningful opportunity to increase   margins 26 Strategically aligned partners, platform for synergies, and   compelling value proposition </font></p>    </td>   </tr>  </table>
